## Severity
Major
## Dimension
complexity
## Location
src/cli/repl/slash.rs:290-345, src/cli/repl/slash.rs:347-398
## Violation
Both functions mix git-status probing, prompt formatting, blocking stdin reads, branching commit flows, push handling, and gh-PR creation in a single linear stretch. Quoted lines:

    if line.trim().to_lowercase().starts_with('y') {
        let _ = Command::new("git").args(["add", "-A"]).output();
        println!("All changes staged.");
    } else { println!("Commit cancelled."); return SlashCommandResult::Handled; }
    ...
    let msg = if file_list.len() == 1 { format!("Update {}", file_list[0]) } else { format!("Update {} files", file_list.len()) };

slash_commit's V(G) >= 15 (is_inside_work_tree, has_staged, has_unstaged, multi-arm prompt over y/yes/empty/e/edit/default, nested Ok/Err arms). Functions are >50 lines, block stdin (no TUI/scripted reuse), and silently `git add -A` (contradicts project commit-quality and safety guidance).
## Mandated refactor
Extract a Commit struct/builder: `Commit::new().prompt_for_staging(&prompt)?.synthesise_message()?.commit()?`. Hoist all stdin behind `trait Prompt { fn confirm(&self, q: &str) -> bool; fn read_line(&self, q: &str) -> String; }` so tests + TUI can drive the same code. Compose slash_commit_push_pr into a Pipeline of Commit/Push/GhPr stages. Replace `git add -A` with an explicit list from `git status --porcelain`, opt-in for untracked files.
## Filed from QA review dispatch
